%I A396809 #15 Jun 13 2026 06:20:58
%S A396809 1,1,4,45,2062,518377
%N A396809 Number of join-hull commutative convexities on a set of n elements.
%C A396809 A convexity C on a set X is a collection of subsets of X such that {} and X are in C, C is closed under arbitrary intersection, and C is closed under directed union.
%C A396809 Every subset S under a convexity C admits a minimal convex superset, which we denote by conv(S).
%C A396809 A convexity C is said to be join-hull commutative (JHC) if for all p in X and A in C, the union of conv({p,x}) over x in A is a convex set.
%H A396809 Victor Chepoi, <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/2407147_Separation_Of_Two_Convex_Sets_In_Convexity_Structures">Separation of Two Convex Sets in Convexity Structures</a>
%H A396809 Tian Vlasic, <a href="/A396809/a396809.py.txt">Python program</a>
%H A396809 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Closure_operator">Closure operator</a>
%F A396809 It is well known that every JHC convexity is interval, hence a(n)<=A364656(n).
%e A396809 The a(3) = 45 set-systems are the following ({} and {1,2,3} not shown).
